DAY 1
SIMPLE OBJECTS: STRINGS, INTEGERS, FLOATS, BOOLEANS
CONDITIONALS (IF)
EVERYTHING IN PYTHON IS AN OBJECT
MEMORY ALLOCATION FOR VARIABLES

IMPORTANT
STRINGS ARE IMMUTABLE SEQUENCES OF CHARACTERS

DAY2

SIMPLE DATA STRUCTURES: LISTS, TUPLES, SETS
METHODS FOR SIMPLE DATA STRUCTURES
LOOPS: FOR, WHILE

IMPORTANT
ORDERED DATA STRUCTURES/ UNORDERED DATA STRUCTURES (SETS) ---> ITERABLES
LISTS : MUTABLE
my_list = [["Anna", "Augustin"],["Maya", "Moses"]]
SETS : MUTABLE, BUT ELEMENTS INSIDE ARE IMMUTABLE
my_set = {["Anna", "Augustin"]}


